  "text": "The Rust internal compiler error (ICE) during trait method resolution occurs in the interaction between candidate collection and ambiguity reporting during trait method resolution.\n\n**Candidate Collection Phase:**\nThe primary collector of trait method candidates is in `compiler/rustc_hir_typeck/src/method/probe.rs`. The `ProbeContext` struct maintains two candidate collections:\n- `inherent_candidates`: collected via `ProbeContext::assemble_inherent_candidates()` which iterates through autoderef steps and assembles probes for each step\n- `extension_candidates`: collected via trait assembly methods including `ProbeContext::assemble_extension_candidates_for_all_traits()` and `ProbeContext::assemble_extension_candidates_for_trait()` which assemble candidates from trait implementations\n\nCandidates are pushed into these collections via `ProbeContext::push_candidate()` (line 781). Each `Candidate<'tcx>` struct wraps a `ty::AssocItem` along with metadata like import IDs and candidate kind.\n\nThe core candidate evaluation happens in `ProbeContext::consider_candidates()` (line 1676), which filters candidates and applies various resolution rules including the shadowing and subtrait logic at lines 1707-1737. When multiple candidates remain after filtering at line 1707, the code attempts to collapse them via `collapse_candidates_to_trait_pick()` and `collapse_candidates_to_subtrait_pick()`. If collapse fails and multiple candidates remain, line 1741 returns `MethodError::Ambiguity(sources)`.\n\n**Ambiguity Error Reporting:**\nAmbiguous trait method errors are reported in two key locations:\n\n1. **Method error handling** in `compiler/rustc_hir_typeck/src/method/suggest.rs` (line 221) where `MethodError::Ambiguity` is caught and an E0034 error (\"multiple applicable items in scope\") is reported with diagnostic information via `note_candidates_on_method_error()`.\n\n2. **Trait-level ambiguity** in `compiler/rustc_trait_selection/src/error_reporting/traits/ambiguity.rs` which provides deeper diagnostic support:\n   - `compute_applicable_impls_for_diagnostics()` (line 31) collects all applicable trait implementations for a given obligation by checking which impls satisfy the trait predicate\n   - `TypeErrCtxt::maybe_report_ambiguity()` (line 160) determines whether to emit an ambiguity error and reports E0283/E0284 errors\n   - `TypeErrCtxt::annotate_source_of_ambiguity()` (line 659) adds detailed annotations about where ambiguity arises from impls vs. bounds\n\nThe trait candidate assembly in `compiler/rustc_trait_selection/src/traits/select/candidate_assembly.rs` at `SelectionContext::assemble_candidates()` (line 27) performs the lower-level trait obligation candidate assembly and sets the `ambiguous` flag on the `SelectionCandidateSet` when appropriate.\n\n**ICE Location:**\nThe ICE in trait method resolution (as documented in test case `tests/crashes/139387.rs` which references issue #139387) occurs at the intersection where multiple trait methods with the same name from different traits (e.g., `fn method()` in both trait A and trait B) create an ambiguous situation. The issue involves the candidate collection not properly handling cases where bound variables and complex trait predicates interact during resolution, potentially causing a panic or ICE in the candidate filtering or collapse logic."
}

